Franz Nahrada:

"I got to know Fillipe through the Clear Village Workshop in Barcelona. Filipe is part of a new breed of young, visionary architects, who see architecture as a vehicle for shaping a sustainable global future. After creating works for architects such as Rem Koolhaas and Thomas Sandell, Filipe is working on his own vision of Evolutionary Architecture, which uses his profession as an instrument to accelerate global development. By prototyping, strategizing, visualizing problems and strategizing solutions, he hopes to create models and processes that can be spread and shared, to be a catalyst for incremental change."


